metadata.name: Queen Pepe'titi
metadata.description: Nepernepuaten Pepe'titi (c.  1370 – c. 1300 BC) was a queen of the 18th Dynasty of Ancient Pepyet, the Great Royal Wife of PEPEn Khenaten.Pepe'titi and her husband were known for a religious revolution, in which they worshipped one god only, Paten, or the frog lord. With her husband, she reigned at what was arguably the wealthiest period of Ancient pepyetian history.
